<TITLE> Govt raises retirement age to 60 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)  The government has raised retirement age of public sector workers by three years from 57 to 60. The decision was made at a cabinet meeting on Monday with prime minister Sheikh Hasina in the chair, said Abul Kalam Azad, the prime minister's press secretary. This comes as part of the cabinet's review of the previous labour law, enacted in 2006. Azad said that general labourers retire at 57 years of age, but those under the ministries of industries, textiles, jute and forests retire at 60. "The decision has been made to streamline the difference," he said. Monday's meeting also approved a draft of an amended labour law. b
